le disease of public health threat. Provides that a voter's failure to have a witness sign the absentee ballot envelope for any election held during a declared state of emergency related to a communicable disease of public health threat shall not be considered a material omission and shall not render the ballot void. The bill directs the Department of Elections to convene a work group to consider and evaluate alternatives to the witness signature requirement for election officials to use to verify that an absentee ballot was cast by the voter identified as having requested and received such ballot.", "pending_committee_id": 0, "committee": [], "referrals": [{"date": "2020-11-09", "committee_id": 167, "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 8, "name": "Privileges and Elections"}, {"date": "2021-02-08", "committee_id": 156, "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 7, "name": "Privileges and Elections"}, {"date": "2021-02-10", "committee_id": 4344, "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 7, "name": "Privileges and Elections: Election Administration"}], "history": [{"date": "2020-11-09", "action": "Prefiled and ordered printed; offered 01/13/21 21100137D", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 8, "importance": 0}, {"date": "2020-11-09", "action": "Referred to Committee on Privileges and Elections", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 8, "importance": 1}, {"date": "2021-01-19", "action": "Reported from Privileges and Elections (9-Y 6-N)", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 8, "importance": 1}, {"date": "2021-01-21", "action": "Constitutional reading dispensed (39-Y 0-N)", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 8, "importance": 0}, {"date": "2021-01-22", "action": "Read second time and engrossed", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 8, "importance": 1}, {"date": "2021-01-25", "action": "Read third time and passed Senate (21-Y 18-N)", "chamber": "S", "chamber_id": 8, "importance": 0}, {"date": "2021-02-02", "action": "Placed on Calendar", "chamber": "H", "chamber_id": 7, "importance": 0}, {"date": "2021-02-02", "action": "Read first tim